AD  - Guilin University of Electronic Technology, Guangxi, Guilin, China
AB  - This study takes the Zhuang bronze drum as the research object, combines memetics and digital technology theory, constructs a theoretical model of intangible cultural heritage inheritance and innovation, and proposes a systematic digital practice strategy. Through literature analysis, field investigation and user experiment, the core meme characteristics and propagation rules of bronze drum culture are identified, and the key factors affecting its contemporary inheritance are analyzed. The research proposes a digital solution represented by the ' Bronze Drum Interactive Drum App Device ', and realizes the modern translation and dissemination of cultural memes through multi-modal interaction design. The research results show that the digital strategy based on memetics can effectively enhance the communication effectiveness and inheritance vitality of intangible cultural heritage, and provide theoretical support and practical reference for the sustainable development of national cultural heritage.  © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
