AB  - The proceedings contain 28 papers. The special focus in this conference is on Theory of Complex Networks and Multilayer Networks. The topics include: Spanning edge betweenness in practice; predictive partitioning for efficient bfs traversal in social networks; temporal multi-layer network construction from major news events; sensitivity of network controllability to weight-based edge thresholding; where is my next friend? recommending enjoyable profiles in location based services; particle filtering as a modeling tool for anomaly detection in networks; the marginal benefit of monitor placement on networks; analysis of the temporal and structural features of threads in a mailing-list; incorporation of social features in the naming game for community detection; a novel approach to evaluate community detection algorithms on ground truth; improving network community structure with link prediction ranking; a subgraph-based ranking system for professional tennis players; modeling memetics using edge diversity; growing networks through random walks without restarts; modeling evolutionary dynamics of lurking in social networks; the network of genetic admixture in humans; network science and narratives; mental lexicon growth modelling reveals the multiplexity of the english language; circadian patterns on wikipedia edits; lyric-based music recommendation; identifying key opinion leaders in evolving co-authorship networks-a descriptive study of a proxy variable for betweenness centrality; forecasting a global air passenger demand network using weighted similarity-based algorithms; influence and sentiment homophily on twitter social circles and comparative network analysis using kronfit.
