AB  - This entry provides an overview of the concept of social contagion, including attention given to both emotional and behavioral forms of contagion. The history of social contagion processes and the various definitions are discussed, as are forms of contagion, including fads and the clustering of both violent and self-injurious behaviors. Also considered is an analysis of the related group processes that influence contagion. Finally, the implications of contagion processes for mental health are discussed as a means of preventing contagious clusters of suicide, eating disorders, instances of violence, and self-harm. © 2023 Elsevier Inc. All rights reserved.
