AB  - Anthropology is the science that studies mankind within the culture and its products. Neuroanthropology more specifically studies the evolution of the nervous system in primates and the influence of culture. Classical neurology has shown little interest regarding cultural aspects and the evolutionary basis of the nervous system. However, this data is important when we interpret the semiology of brain injury in neurological patients and when interpreting neurological diseases within a cultural context. This review presents some data on the field of neuroanthropology in order to enrich the context within which the clinical neurologist works.
