AD  - Brunei University, Brunei Darussalam
AB  - This chapter illustrates that the target memetics is attempting to inform - culture - is itself incoherent. It also states that culture used to be linked with the aristocratic notion of 'civilized taste', but now commonly implies 'shared beliefs'. It proposes that Dawkins' ideas about culture are a reversion to an earlier and happier time. Culture traits are not the equivalent of philosophical notions, and even when ideas are in question, their ecology is not made up only or even primarily by other ideas. The final objection to the whole memes industry is that it has yet to deliver a single original and plausible analysis of any cultural or social process. © Oxford University Press, 2000. All rights reserved.
