AD  - Center for Languages, Cultures, and Regional Studies, US Military Academy at West Point, United States
AB  - Teaching second language/culture (L2/C2) in beginning Russian classrooms is often difficult given time constraints of curriculum and students’ limited proficiency. This chapter explores the use of Russian-language pop-music videos with bilingual subtitles on an online video platform to raise awareness of contemporary Russian-language culture in beginning-level college Russian. In contrast to other approaches that “contextualize” aspects of high culture into simplified learning materials for beginning learners, this approach allows teachers to harness a creative content-based medium that is culturally relevant and user-, time-, and resource-friendly. This chapter shows how the visual and textual memetics (Borenstein, 2004, 2022) of pop-music videos can provide authentic and highly memorable cultural insights into Russian language and culture. The initial student perceptions and learning outcomes of this content-based approach are analyzed from the perspective of the ACTFL World Readiness Standards for Learning Languages (NSCB, 2015) through a self-report survey with open-ended and Likert-scaled questions administered to students at the end of the course. © 2025 selection and editorial matter, Jason Merrill, Olga Makarova, and Svetlana V. Nuss.
