AB  - Computer aided instruction is widely used as an advanced teaching technique. This paper makes an empirical analysis of vocabulary teaching in college English based on computer-assisted memetics. The quantity and quality of vocabulary accumulated will directly affect college students' language skills, as well as the effectiveness and efficiency of foreign language teaching. Memetics is an important language theory based on the theory of cultural evolution, which mainly focuses on vocabulary meme replication and transmission in the process of English vocabulary teaching. This paper will adopt empirical analysis method to explore vocabulary memetics teaching by using computer assisted multimedia platform, trying to test the effectiveness of this model. For this purpose, two non-English major classes will be selected randomly for study. One is the experimental class where meme theory is carried out. The other is the control class where traditional teaching method is performed. The results of the experiment will be recorded and analyzed to verify the positive role meme theory in the College English Vocabulary Teaching.
